plementations, or other class definitions that are only discovered after the native executable is built, accept the `NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(e)` catch pattern from `org.graalvm.internal.tck`. Reject raw native-only skips, bare `catch (Error)` blocks, and use of this pattern for ordinary reflection, resources, serialization, dynamic proxies, JNI, or missing reachability metadata.\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:35:   - Expected files are usually limited to the target coordinate's generated new-version support:\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:42:   - Treat generated test project files such as `.gitignore`, `build.gradle`, `gradle.properties`, `settings.gradle`, and `user-code-filter.json` as normal when they live under the target version's test directory.\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:44:   - Be suspicious of unrelated build logic, workflows, generated sources, other libraries, or broad refactors.\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:45:   - Reject legacy native-image metadata config files. Metadata for generated support and test-only metadata must use `reachability-metadata.json`.\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:62:   - If stats are missing or stale, ask for `generateLibraryStats` or the relevant CI stats job before approving.\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:69:   - Do not require an exact match. Differences are normal when upstream APIs move, generated metadata is cleaned up, or dynamic-access totals change.\n./skills/review-fixes-java-run-fail/SKILL.md:119:- For missing stats: ask for regenerated library stats or CI evidence before approval.\nbuild/reports/problems/problems-report.html:653:{\"diagnostics\":[{\"locations\":[{\"path\":\"/home/vjovanov/c/forge/forge1/graalvm-reachability-metadata/forge/local_repositories/forge_worktrees/2259-1c1c91f0/tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/stats/LibraryStatsSupport.java\"},{\"taskPath\":\":compile