\",\"displayName\":\"Invocation of Task.project at execution time has been deprecated.\"}],\"solutions\":[[{\"text\":\"This API is incompatible with the configuration cache, which will become the only mode supported by Gradle in a future release.\"}]]},{\"locations\":[{\"taskPath\":\":discoverArtifactMetadata\"}],\"problem\":[{\"text\":\"Invocation of Task.project at execution time has been deprecated.\"}],\"severity\":\"WARNING\",\"problemDetails\":[{\"text\":\"This will fail with an error in Gradle 10.\"}],\"contextualLabel\":\"Invocation of Task.project at execution time has been deprecated.\",\"documentationLink\":\"https://docs.gradle.org/9.1.0/userguide/upgrading_version_7.html#task_project\",\"problemId\":[{\"name\":\"deprecation\",\"displayName\":\"Deprecation\"},{\"name\":\"invocation-of-task-project-at-execution-time\",\"displayName\":\"Invocation of Task.project at execution time has been deprecated.\"}],\"solutions\":[[{\"text\":\"This API is incompatible with the configuration cache, which will become the only mode supported by Gradle in a future release.\"}]]},{\"locations\":[{\"taskPath\":\":discoverArtifactMetadata\"}],\"problem\":[{\"text\":\"Invocation of Task.project at execution time has been deprecated.\"}],\"severity\":\"WARNING\",\"problemDetails\":[{\"text\":\"This will fail with an error in Gradle 10.\"}],\"contextualLabel\":\"Invocation of Task.project at execution time has been deprecated.\",\"documentationLink\":\"https://docs.gradle.org/9.1.0/userguide/upgrading_version_7.html#task_project\",\"problemId\":[{\"name\":\"deprecation\",\"displayName\":\"Deprecation\"},{\"name\":\"invocation-of-task-project-at-execution-time\",\"displayName\":\"Invocation of Task.project at execution time has been deprecated.\"}],\"solutions\":[[{\"text\":\"This API is incompatible with the configuration cache, which will become the only mode supported by Gradle in a future release.\"}]]}],\"problemsReport\":{\"totalProblemCount\":10,\"buildName\":\"reachability-metadata\",\"requestedTasks\":\"discoverArtifactMetadata --coordinates=org.scalatest:scalatest-freespec_3:3.2.19 --agent-command=codex -a never exec -s danger-full-access\",\"documentationLink\":\"https://docs.gradle.org/9.1.0/userguide/reporting_problems.html\",\"documentationLinkCaption\":\"Problem report\",\"summaries\":[]}}\n./skills/review-library-new-request/SKILL.md:18:- Do not accept scaffold-only tests. Generated tests must be changed into library-specific tests that exercise the behavior that requires the metadata.\n./skills/review-library-new-request/SKILL.md:19:- Tests should execute under native image by default. Do not accept tests that disable themselves under native image. When a test exercises behavior that fundamentally relies on open-ended dynamic class loading that native image cannot support, such as loading classes, JARs, generated bytecode, plugin implementations, or other class definitions that are only discovered after the native executable is built, accept the `NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(e)` catch pattern from `org.graalvm.internal.tck`. Reject raw native-only skips, bare `catch (Error)` blocks, and use of this pattern for ordinary reflection, resources, serialization, dynamic proxies, JNI, or missing reachability metadata.\n./skills/review-library-new-request/SKILL.md:42:   - Be suspicious of changes to build logic, workflows, unrelated libraries, generated sources outside the target test directory, or wide refactors.\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/FixTestNativeImageRun.java:28: * It regenerates reachability metadata for the specified library version and updates the\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/FixTestNativeImageRun.java:106:        verifyGeneratedMetadata(metadataDirectory);\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/FixTestNativeImageRun.java:124:            verifyGeneratedMetadata(metadataDirectory);\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/FixTestNativeImageRun.java:132:    private void verifyGeneratedMetadata(Path metadataDirectory) {\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:16:- Expect compile-focused changes plus the normal generated support files for the newly tested version: test source updates, imports, renamed APIs, dependency adjustments, a new metadata-version directory, stats, and metadata index changes.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:19:- Native-image execution should remain enabled by default when the repaired test reaches the native lane. Do not accept changes that skip or short-circuit native-image behavior. When a test exercises behavior that fundamentally relies on open-ended dynamic class loading that native image cannot support, such as loading classes, JARs, generated bytecode, plugin implementations, or other class definitions that are only discovered after the native executable is built, accept the `NativeImageSupport.isUnsupportedFeatureError(e)` catch pattern from `org.graalvm.internal.tck`. Reject raw native-only skips, bare `catch (Error)` blocks, and use of this pattern for ordinary reflection, resources, serialization, dynamic proxies, JNI, or missing reachability metadata.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:35:   - Expected files are usually limited to the target coordinate's generated new-version support:\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:42:   - Treat generated test project files such as `.gitignore`, `build.gradle`, `gradle.properties`, `settings.gradle`, and `user-code-filter.json` as normal when they live under the target version's test directory.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:43:   - Be suspicious of unrelated build logic, workflows, generated sources, other libraries, or broad refactors.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:44:   - Reject legacy native-image metadata config files. Metadata for generated support and test-only metadata must use `reachability-metadata.json`.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:60:   - If stats are missing or stale, ask for `generateLibraryStats` or the relevant CI stats job before approving.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:67:   - Do not require an exact match. Differences are normal when upstream APIs move, generated metadata is cleaned up, or dynamic-access totals change.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:115:- For missing stats: ask for regenerated library stats or CI evidence before approval.\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:146:void loadsGeneratedHandlerClass() throws Exception {\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:149:        assertThat(HandlerRegistry.register(handlerClass).name()).isEqualTo(\"generated\");\n./skills/review-fixes-javac-fail/SKILL.md:154:        // Expected: Native Image cannot load generated classes discovered after build.\n./docs/CONTRIBUTING.md:37:- generate necessary boilerplate code\n./docs/CONTRIBUTING.md:39:- generate metadata and store it in the proper location\n./docs/CONTRIBUTING.md:42:If you already have the test project structure in this repository and need to generate or regenerate metadata, use the `generateMetadata` task:\n./docs/CONTRIBUTING.md:45:./gradlew generateMetadata --coordinates=com.example:my-library:1.0.0\n./docs/CONTRIBUTING.md:51:./gradlew generateMetadata --coordinates=com.example:my-library:1.0.0 --agentAllowedPackages=fromJar\n./docs/CONTRIBUTING.md:52:./gradlew generateMetadata --coordinates=com.example:my-library:1.0.0 --agentAllowedPackages=com.example.pkg,org.acme.lib\n./docs/CONTRIBUTING.md:72:### Generate Metadata and Test\n./docs/CONTRIBUTING.md:74:Use the `scaffold` task to generate metadata and test stubs:\n./docs/CONTRIBUTING.md:88:It's expected that they fail, because the scaffold task only generated a stub which you need to implement.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:23:- Prefer concrete evidence from native run output, generated metadata, stats, and CI over style objections.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:40:   - Treat generated test project files such as `.gitignore`, `build.gradle`, `gradle.properties`, `settings.gradle`, and `user-code-filter.json` as normal when they live under the target version's test directory.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:43:   - Be suspicious of unrelated build logic, workflows, generated sources, other libraries, or broad refactors.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:44:   - Reject legacy native-image metadata config files. Metadata for generated support and test-only metadata must use `reachability-metadata.json`.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:49:   - Metadata additions should be specific enough to the target library behavior; do not require hand-minimized entries when generated metadata is coherent and validation passes.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:60:   - If stats are missing or stale, ask for `generateLibraryStats` or the relevant CI stats job before approving.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:67:   - Do not require an exact match. Differences are normal when upstream APIs move, generated metadata is cleaned up, or dynamic-access totals change.\n./skills/review-fixes-native-image-run-fail/SKILL.md:112:- For missing stats: ask for regenerated library stats or CI evidence before approval.\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/utils/MetadataGenerationUtils.java:201:     * they are not test-only merely because a generated test provided a stub.\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/utils/MetadataGenerationUtils.java:264:     * Runs Gradle tasks to generate metadata using the agent and then copies\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/utils/MetadataGenerationUtils.java:270:            Path agentMetadataDirectory = Files.createTempDirectory(\"generate-metadata-agent-\");\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/utils/MetadataGenerationUtils.java:271:            Path mergedMetadataDirectory = Files.createTempDirectory(\"generate-metadata-merged-\");\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/utils/MetadataGenerationUtils.java:285:     * Runs Gradle tasks to generate metadata using the agent and copies\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/utils/MetadataGenerationUtils.java:292:        GeneralUtils.invokeCommand(execOps, gradlew.toString(), List.of(\"-Pagent\", \"test\"), \"Cannot generate metadata\", testsDirectory);\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/utils/MetadataGenerationUtils.java:299:     * Runs Gradle tasks to generate metadata using the agent with a specific GVM_TCK_LV\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/utils/MetadataGenerationUtils.java:305:            Path agentMetadataDirectory = Files.createTempDirectory(\"generate-metadata-agent-\");\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/utils/MetadataGenerationUtils.java:306:            Path mergedMetadataDirectory = Files.createTempDirectory(\"generate-metadata-merged-\");\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/utils/MetadataGenerationUtils.java:320:     * Runs Gradle tasks to generate metadata using the agent with a specific GVM_TCK_LV\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/utils/MetadataGenerationUtils.java:329:        GeneralUtils.invokeCommand(execOps, gradlew.toString(), List.of(\"-Pagent\", \"test\"), env, \"Cannot generate metadata\", testsDirectory);\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/utils/MetadataGenerationUtils.java:353:        GeneralUtils.printInfo(\"Merging generated metadata\");\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/utils/MetadataGenerationUtils.java:362:                \"Cannot merge generated metadata\",\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/utils/MetadataGenerationUtils.java:403:            if (!matchesGeneratedCoordinate(entry, coordinates)) {\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/utils/MetadataGenerationUtils.java:427:    private static boolean matchesGeneratedCoordinate(Map<String, Object> entry, Coordinates coordinates) {\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:22:| **Repository automation (Metadata Forge)** | Generate or repair metadata using LLM-driven pipelines. | Per coordinate, the toolkit can: (1) **add support for a new library** — generate a JUnit / Kotlin / Scala test suite, scaffold metadata, and iterate until JVM-mode tests pass and dynamic-access is collected ([`add_new_library_support.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/add_new_library_support.py)); (2) **fix a Java compilation (`javac`) failure** raised by a library version bump ([`fix_javac_fail.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_javac_fail.py)); (3) **fix a JVM-mode (`javaTest`) runtime failure** raised by a version bump ([`fix_java_run_fail.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_java_run_fail.py)); (4) **fix a `native-image` runtime failure** raised by a version bump ([`fix_ni_run.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_ni_run.py)); (5) **improve dynamic-access coverage** of already-supported libraries by targeting uncovered call sites; (6) **post-generation repair** of the metadata produced by a previous run ([`fix_post_generation_pi.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_post_generation_pi.py), [`fix_metadata_codex.py`](../forge/ai_workflows/fix_metadata_codex.py)). Each task runs Gradle tasks against a worktree of this repo, appends a schema-validated metrics record, and — when invoked through [`forge/git_scripts/make_pr_*.py`](../forge/git_scripts/) — opens a PR for human review. See [forge/docs/architecture.md](../forge/docs/architecture.md). |\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:57:The harness uses a single coordinates filter `-Pcoordinates=` accepting `all`, `group:artifact`, `group:artifact:version`, or shard `k/n`. It also exposes authoring helpers (`generateMetadata`, `splitTestOnlyMetadata`, `fixTestNativeImageRun`, `addTestedVersion`, `fetchExistingLibrariesWithNewerVersions`), reporting tasks (`jacocoTestReport`, `generateDynamicAccessCoverageReport`, `generateLibraryStats`, `analyzeExternalLibraryDynamicAccess`), and the `package` release task. The full task reference lives in [DEVELOPING.md](DEVELOPING.md).\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:83:sync with the generated coverage table. The same `COVERAGE.md` and the badge,\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:89:1. **Add new library support** — generate a JUnit test suite, scaffold metadata, iterate until JVM-mode tests pass and dynamic-access metadata is collected.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:116:| `GenAI` | PR | PR was produced by generative-AI automation. Generated PR titles also use a `[GenAI]` prefix when created by the corresponding Forge scripts. |\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:269:- Metadata JSON files contributed by a human or generated by Forge.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:270:- Test sources contributed by a human or generated by Forge.\n./docs/FUNCTIONAL_SPEC.md:277:- Mirrored stats under `stats/`, a generated root `COVERAGE.md`, and aggregated coverage artifacts on `stats/coverage`.\ntests/tck-build-logic/src/main/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/FixTestNativeImageRun.java:28: * It regenerates reachability metadata for the specified library version and updates the\ntests/tck-build-logic/src/main/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/FixTestNativeImageRun.java:106:        verifyGeneratedMetadata(metadataDirectory);\ntests/tck-build-logic/src/main/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/FixTestNativeImageRun.java:124:            verifyGeneratedMetadata(metadataDirectory);\ntests/tck-build-logic/src/main/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/FixTestNativeImageRun.java:132:    private void verifyGeneratedMetadata(Path metadataDirectory) {\n./docs/CollectingMetadata.md:2:When the repository doesn’t have reachability metadata for a library you are using, the easiest way to generate it is to execute the test suite of the library with the Native Image Agent enabled. The agent is installed together with native-image and can be used to identify elements used during application execution that cannot be discovered by static analysis.\n./docs/CollectingMetadata.md:26:To run the test task with the agent, run `./gradlew -Pagent` test. This will generate metadata in the build output directory of the project (under `build/native/agent/test`).\n./docs/CollectingMetadata.md:30:The conditional mode requires the users to pass an agent filter file that tells the agent which classes belong to the target library. This filter file has the same format as other agent filter files. Conditions will only be generated on classes whose names are matched by this filter.\n./docs/CollectingMetadata.md:59:Conditional metadata can be generated by inserting the Native Image Agent options into the command line of the JVM that runs the tests.\n./docs/CollectingMetadata.md:73:native-image-configure generate-conditional --user-code-filter=user-code-filter.json --class-name-filter=extra-code-filter.json --input-dir=<agent-output-dir> --input-dir=<agent-output-dir-2>... --output-dir=final-metadata/\n./docs/CollectingMetadata.md:80:The best thing for the community is to include the generated metadata and build file changes into the library itself. Before creating a PR to the library:\n./gradle/checkstyle.xml:213:            <property name=\"offCommentFormat\" value=\"CheckStyle: start generated\"/>\n./gradle/checkstyle.xml:214:            <property name=\"onCommentFormat\" value=\"CheckStyle: stop generated\"/>\n./docs/CI.md:19:- Gradle tasks read it to generate GitHub Actions matrices consumed by the workflows below.\n./docs/CI.md:25:  - Uses: generateMatrixBatchedCoordinates with 85 batches to build a matrix (java + os). Runs full tests, pulls only allowed Docker images, then disables Docker networking for deterministic runs. Failed batches are isolated down to concrete library versions and reported as aggregated GitHub issues across the configured GraalVM JDK/OS combinations and native-image modes.\n./docs/CI.md:28:  - Uses: [`generateChangedMetadataTestMatrix`](../tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org.graalvm.internal.tck-harness.gradle) with base/head SHAs to test only what changed. It batches each changed metadata version's [`tested-versions`](../metadata/com.google.protobuf/protobuf-java-util/index.json) into chunks of up to 30 versions per job, includes newly added tested versions from artifact-level index diffs, then pulls allowed images, disables Docker networking, validates config, and runs only that batch.\n./docs/CI.md:31:  - Uses: generateInfrastructureChangedCoordinatesMatrix. Pulls allowed images, disables Docker networking, validates config, then runs tests.\n./docs/CI.md:34:  - Uses: generateAffectedSpringTestMatrix to compute impacted Spring AOT projects and produce a matrix; runs triaged native tests via [.github/workflows/scripts/run-spring-aot-triaged-test.sh](../.github/workflows/scripts/run-spring-aot-triaged-test.sh).\n./docs/CI.md:40:  - Uses: [`fetchExistingLibrariesWithNewerVersions`](../tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org.graalvm.internal.tck-harness.gradle) plus [`generateNewLibraryVersionCompatibilityMatrix`](../tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/groovy/org.graalvm.internal.tck-harness.gradle) to build a [`ci.json`](../ci.json)-driven matrix. The matrix generator limits the number of libraries per run, limits each library to at most 30 newer versions per run before expanding across the configured GraalVM JDK/OS combinations, records tested versions only after they pass on every required environment, and creates a single aggregated failure issue per failed library version while preserving the prior failure issue format with added OS and JDK lines.\n./docs/CI.md:46:- [.github/workflows/publish-scheduled-coverage.yml](../.github/workflows/publish-scheduled-coverage.yml): scheduled/manual workflow that generates repository coverage badges and the coverage dashboard from exploded stats files under [stats/](../stats/) and repository [metadata/**/index.json](../metadata/). It commits the generated [COVERAGE.md](../COVERAGE.md) back to the source branch, including links from versions to artifact index files and from coverage values to artifact stats directories, then force-pushes the published artifacts to the `stats/coverage` branch. The published branch only keeps `COVERAGE.md`, `latest/badges.json`, `latest/metrics-over-time.svg`, `latest/metrics-over-time-dark.svg`, and `history/history.json`.\n./docs/CI.md:56:Once eligible, the workflow extracts the requested Maven coordinates from the issue title, validates the `groupId:artifactId:version` format, closes invalid requests, closes duplicate exact-coordinate requests, and closes requests for versions already supported by the repository. If the request remains eligible, it generates a deps.dev dependency graph and opens or reuses `library-new-request` issues for unsupported transitive dependencies, linking them as blockers of the original request.\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/GenerateMetadataTask.java:27: * Generates metadata for the given library coordinates and, if packages list is provided, creates a new user-code-filter.json.\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/GenerateMetadataTask.java:29:public abstract class GenerateMetadataTask extends DefaultTask {\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/GenerateMetadataTask.java:71:    @Option(option = \"metadataOutputDir\", description = \"Directory where generated agent metadata is copied without durable final merge\")\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/GenerateMetadataTask.java:93:            // Fresh scaffolds have no agent block; default to library group package so conditional metadata can be generated.\n./tests/tck-build-logic/src/main/java/org/graalvm/internal/tck/Ch